---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Linear Migration · Mollie Cox"
  description="Migrating an engineering org from Jira to Linear. 2.7x throughput, 87 to 93% cycle completion, 5.0/5 satisfaction."
>
  <!-- ============================== -->
  <!-- HERO -->
  <!-- ============================== -->
  <section class="case-hero-dark">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-20 md:py-28 relative z-10">
      <a
        href="/#work"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cream/60 hover:text-orange transition-colors mb-16"
      >
        ← All work
      </a>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-12 items-start">

        <!-- Text column -->
        <div class="md:col-span-7">
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-6">Branch · Spring 2026</p>

          <h1 class="font-display text-display-lg text-cream leading-[0.95] tracking-tight">
            Migrating an engineering org from Jira to Linear<span class="brand-period">.</span>
          </h1>

          <p class="mt-10 text-xl text-cream/80 leading-relaxed max-w-[48ch]">
            A six-week pilot with real engineers, not a vendor demo. The data made the
            case. 2.7x throughput, 87 to 93% cycle completion, and the team voting
            overwhelmingly to migrate.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Artifact column: two trajectories diverging -->
        <div class="md:col-span-5 flex justify-center md:justify-end items-start mt-8 md:mt-0">
          <div class="case-hero-artifact w-full max-w-sm md:max-w-none">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 480 440" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="Two trajectories diverging from a single decision point, one flat dashed line representing keeping Jira, one solid orange path ascending sharply representing the move to Linear">

              <!-- Subtle grid backdrop -->
              <g opacity="0.06">
                <line stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="0.5" x1="80" y1="20" x2="80" y2="420"/>
                <line stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="0.5" x1="160" y1="20" x2="160" y2="420"/>
                <line stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="0.5" x1="240" y1="20" x2="240" y2="420"/>
                <line stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="0.5" x1="320" y1="20" x2="320" y2="420"/>
                <line stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="0.5" x1="400" y1="20" x2="400" y2="420"/>
              </g>

              <!-- Origin / decision point -->
              <circle cx="60" cy="300" r="12" fill="#02101D" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="3"/>
              <circle cx="60" cy="300" r="4" fill="#E13D0F"/>

              <!-- Jira path: flat, dashed, faint -->
              <path d="M 60 300 C 180 300, 280 312, 440 320" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.35" stroke-dasharray="7 7"/>
              <circle cx="440" cy="320" r="6" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.5"/>
              <text x="430" y="352" fill="#F4EFE5" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11" letter-spacing="2.5" opacity="0.5" text-anchor="end">JIRA · KEEP</text>

              <!-- Linear path: solid orange, ascending sharply -->
              <path d="M 60 300 C 200 300, 280 200, 440 60" fill="none" stroke="#E13D0F" stroke-width="3.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>

              <!-- Linear endpoint terminator -->
              <circle cx="440" cy="60" r="11" fill="#02101D" stroke="#E13D0F" stroke-width="3.5"/>
              <circle cx="440" cy="60" r="4" fill="#E13D0F"/>
              <text x="430" y="34" fill="#E13D0F" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="13" letter-spacing="2.5" font-weight="500" text-anchor="end">LINEAR · 2.7×</text>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="mt-20 grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 pt-10 border-t border-cream/15 relative z-10">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">Role</p>
          <p class="text-cream">Sr. Director, Product Experience</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">Duration</p>
          <p class="text-cream">12 weeks (setup + pilot)</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">Team</p>
          <p class="text-cream">Eng, PM, Product Ops</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">Outcome</p>
          <p class="text-cream">Enterprise rollout decision</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- The headline result -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="grid-backdrop border-b border-ink/10 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-top"></div>
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-bottom"></div>
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-20 md:py-28 relative z-10">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-12">The result</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-x-6 gap-y-12">
        <div>
          <p class="stat-hero">2.7×</p>
          <p class="stat-hero-label">Throughput gain</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="stat-hero">93%</p>
          <p class="stat-hero-label">Cycle completion</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="stat-hero">5.0</p>
          <p class="stat-hero-label">Engineer satisfaction</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="stat-hero">6wk</p>
          <p class="stat-hero-label">Pilot duration</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- THREE PILLARS: Question · Method · Recommendation -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="pillar-grid">

      <!-- Question -->
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <!-- Forked path / decision -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <circle cx="40" cy="14" r="6" fill="#E13D0F"/>
            <line x1="40" y1="20" x2="40" y2="36" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
            <path d="M40 36 L 20 50 L 20 66" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <path d="M40 36 L 60 50 L 60 66" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <circle cx="20" cy="68" r="5" fill="#E13D0F"/>
            <circle cx="60" cy="68" r="5" fill="#02101D"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-meta">
          <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The question</p>
          <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">
            Fix what we have, or replace it?
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-body">
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            Our Jira instance had years of accumulated complexity. Non-standardized
            issue types, no cross-team initiative visibility, significant abandoned
            space alongside active work. The proposed fix was months of contractor-led
            cleanup. Before signing off, I wanted to test a different question.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-tagline"></div>
      </div>

      <!-- Method -->
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <!-- Scales / measurement -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <line x1="40" y1="14" x2="40" y2="60" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
            <line x1="14" y1="22" x2="66" y2="22" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
            <!-- Left pan -->
            <path d="M14 22 L 8 40 L 26 40 Z" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            <line x1="14" y1="22" x2="14" y2="32" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2"/>
            <!-- Right pan -->
            <path d="M66 22 L 60 40 L 78 40 Z" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            <line x1="66" y1="22" x2="66" y2="32" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2"/>
            <!-- Base -->
            <rect x="30" y="60" width="20" height="6" fill="#02101D"/>
            <circle cx="40" cy="14" r="3" fill="#E13D0F"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-meta">
          <p class="eyebrow-voice mb-3">The method</p>
          <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">
            Real engineers, real work, real data.
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-body">
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            I designed a six-week live pilot. Not a sandbox. Real engineers doing
            real work, benchmarked in both systems. Five target metrics set before
            the pilot started. Issue throughput, satisfaction, cycle completion,
            tracking percentage, resolution time.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-tagline">
          <p class="font-display text-2xl italic text-orange">"The data made the case."</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Recommendation -->
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <!-- Upward arrow / forward motion -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <path d="M40 12 L 60 36 L 50 36 L 50 64 L 30 64 L 30 36 L 20 36 Z" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            <line x1="34" y1="46" x2="46" y2="46" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.6"/>
            <line x1="34" y1="54" x2="46" y2="54" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.6"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-meta">
          <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The recommendation</p>
          <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">
            A capability decision, not a cost cut.
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-body">
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            The financial case wasn't a savings story. It was a capability story.
            Capability decisions survive procurement cycles. Savings decisions get
            re-litigated. The migration moved forward as a full org cut-over with
            white-glove customer success onboarding.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-tagline"></div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- Metrics breakdown -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="bg-cream-warm/40 border-y border-ink/10 py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Five metrics. Four hits. One partial. Zero misses.</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight max-w-[26ch] mb-16">
        The pilot hit every target I set.
      </h2>

      <!-- Throughput visual: before/after bar comparison -->
      <div class="mb-16 p-8 md:p-12 bg-cream border border-ink/10" style="border-radius: 16px;">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-12 items-center">
          <!-- Headline + caption -->
          <div class="md:col-span-4">
            <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Issue creation frequency</p>
            <p class="font-display text-ink leading-none mb-3" style="font-size: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);">2.7×</p>
            <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
              Issues created per engineer per week, baseline measured in Jira against pilot in Linear over six weeks. Target was 2×.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Bar chart -->
          <div class="md:col-span-8">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 600 280" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-full h-auto">
              <!-- Baseline grid lines -->
              <g stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.08">
                <line x1="120" y1="40" x2="600" y2="40"/>
                <line x1="120" y1="100" x2="600" y2="100"/>
                <line x1="120" y1="160" x2="600" y2="160"/>
                <line x1="120" y1="220" x2="600" y2="220"/>
              </g>

              <!-- Jira (before) bar - small, navy -->
              <g>
                <text x="0" y="200" font-family="ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace" font-size="11" fill="#5C6770" letter-spacing="1.5">JIRA</text>
                <text x="0" y="215" font-family="ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace" font-size="10" fill="#5C6770" letter-spacing="0.5" opacity="0.7">BEFORE</text>
                <rect x="120" y="187" width="148" height="34" fill="#02101D" rx="4"/>
                <text x="280" y="210" font-family="ui-serif, Georgia, serif" font-size="20" font-weight="500" fill="#02101D">1.0× baseline</text>
              </g>

              <!-- Linear (after) bar - large, orange -->
              <g>
                <text x="0" y="80" font-family="ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace" font-size="11" fill="#E13D0F" letter-spacing="1.5">LINEAR</text>
                <text x="0" y="95" font-family="ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace" font-size="10" fill="#E13D0F" letter-spacing="0.5" opacity="0.8">AFTER</text>
                <rect x="120" y="67" width="400" height="34" fill="#E13D0F" rx="4"/>
                <text x="532" y="90" font-family="ui-serif, Georgia, serif" font-size="20" font-weight="500" fill="#02101D">2.7× throughput</text>
              </g>

              <!-- Target marker dashed line at 2× point -->
              <g>
                <line x1="416" y1="40" x2="416" y2="240" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4 4" opacity="0.4"/>
                <text x="416" y="32" font-family="ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace" font-size="10" fill="#5C6770" letter-spacing="1.5" text-anchor="middle" opacity="0.8">TARGET 2×</text>
              </g>

              <!-- X axis labels -->
              <g font-family="ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace" font-size="10" fill="#5C6770" letter-spacing="1" opacity="0.6">
                <text x="120" y="262" text-anchor="middle">0</text>
                <text x="268" y="262" text-anchor="middle">1×</text>
                <text x="416" y="262" text-anchor="middle">2×</text>
                <text x="520" y="262" text-anchor="middle">2.7×</text>
              </g>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        {[
          {
            metric: 'Issue creation frequency',
            target: 'Target: 2× increase',
            result: '2.7× throughput per engineer, per week',
            status: 'HIT',
          },
          {
            metric: 'Engineer satisfaction',
            target: 'Target: 4.0+ in Linear',
            result: '5.0/5 overall. Every dimension above 4.0.',
            status: 'HIT',
          },
          {
            metric: 'Cycle completion rate',
            target: 'Target: stable or improved',
            result: '100%, 87%, 93% across first three cycles. Planning 4 cycles ahead.',
            status: 'HIT',
          },
          {
            metric: '% of work tracked',
            target: 'Target: 80%+',
            result: '4 of 5 respondents at 75 to 100%. Most issues tied to a project.',
            status: 'HIT',
          },
          {
            metric: 'Issue resolution time',
            target: 'Target: faster',
            result: 'Median work time under 2 days. Jira baseline unavailable in export.',
            status: 'PARTIAL',
          },
        ].map((row) => (
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-4 py-6 px-6 bg-cream border border-ink/10 items-start" style="border-radius: 12px;">
            <div class="md:col-span-3">
              <p class="font-display text-lg text-ink">{row.metric}</p>
              <p class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-muted mt-1">{row.target}</p>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-7 text-ink-soft">{row.result}</div>
            <div class="md:col-span-2 md:text-right">
              <span
                class={`font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] px-3 py-1 ${
                  row.status === 'HIT' ? 'bg-orange text-cream' : 'bg-cream-warm text-ink'
                }`}
                style="border-radius: 999px;"
              >
                {row.status}
              </span>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- Quote callout -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="bg-ink text-cream py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10">
      <p class="eyebrow-light mb-8">Voice of the engineer</p>
      <blockquote class="font-display text-cream leading-[1.05] tracking-tight max-w-[24ch]" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);">
        "Please let us keep using Linear. I desperately do not want to go back to Jira<span class="text-orange">."</span>
      </blockquote>
      <p class="mt-8 font-mono text-sm text-cream/60 uppercase tracking-wider">Pilot engineer · Post-pilot survey</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- Lessons three-up -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-24 md:py-32">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">What I did</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight max-w-[26ch] mb-16">
      Design leadership isn't just about what ships.
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 md:gap-8">
      <div class="lesson-card">
        <div class="linocut-icon">
          <!-- Magnifier on doc -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <rect x="20" y="14" width="36" height="50" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
            <line x1="26" y1="24" x2="48" y2="24" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2"/>
            <line x1="26" y1="32" x2="48" y2="32" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2"/>
            <line x1="26" y1="40" x2="42" y2="40" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2"/>
            <circle cx="52" cy="52" r="10" fill="#02101D"/>
            <circle cx="52" cy="52" r="6" fill="#F4EFE5"/>
            <line x1="58" y1="58" x2="68" y2="68" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">Framing the right question.</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          Most "tooling decision" stories are project-management fables. The leverage
          is reframing it as capability versus cost, not Jira versus Linear.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="lesson-card">
        <div class="linocut-icon">
          <!-- Trophy / accountability -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <path d="M28 16 L 52 16 L 50 40 C 50 46, 46 50, 40 50 C 34 50, 30 46, 30 40 Z" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            <path d="M28 20 L 18 20 L 18 28 C 18 34, 24 36, 30 36" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <path d="M52 20 L 62 20 L 62 28 C 62 34, 56 36, 50 36" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <rect x="34" y="50" width="12" height="8" fill="#02101D"/>
            <rect x="28" y="58" width="24" height="6" fill="#02101D"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">Holding the test accountable.</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          Five target metrics set before the pilot, not after. Methodology designed
          to be defensible to dissenters. Result presented as a business case.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="lesson-card">
        <div class="linocut-icon">
          <!-- Speech bubble / persuasion -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <path d="M14 22 L 14 50 C 14 54, 18 58, 22 58 L 32 58 L 38 68 L 44 58 L 58 58 C 62 58, 66 54, 66 50 L 66 22 C 66 18, 62 14, 58 14 L 22 14 C 18 14, 14 18, 14 22 Z" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            <line x1="22" y1="28" x2="58" y2="28" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2"/>
            <line x1="22" y1="36" x2="58" y2="36" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2"/>
            <line x1="22" y1="44" x2="46" y2="44" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">Managing the dissent.</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          When the data is too good, the dissent gets sharper. Solution engineering
          sessions to address concerns directly before the cutover decision.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- Meta-point -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="grid-backdrop overflow-hidden border-b border-ink/10">
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-top"></div>
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-bottom"></div>
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-28 md:py-36 relative z-10">
      <p class="eyebrow-voice mb-8">The meta-point</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-ink leading-[0.95] tracking-tight mb-12" style="font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5.5rem);">
        Design leadership isn't just about what ships.<br/>
        <span class="text-orange">It's about what gets decided.</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          Framing the right question. Designing a defensible test methodology.
          Holding it accountable to pre-set metrics. Presenting the result as a
          business case rather than a feature wishlist. That's what design
          leadership at the executive level actually looks like.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
